# Step 00: defensive guard against an old build of the Proscenio
# Exporter plugin re-creating an auto-save PSD next to the manifest.
# The current importer (>= 2a92db3) leaves the doc unsaved on purpose.
00_blender_base/photoshop/

# Step 01: clean re-export of the untagged baseline PSD. Diagnostic
# only (round-trip oracle); the PSD itself IS tracked. Regenerable
# via the Proscenio Exporter panel against doll_ps_base.psd.
01_photoshop_base/export/

# Step 02: UXP export oracle. The captured-baseline subfolder for
# SPEC 010 parity checks; regenerable via the manual procedure in
# specs/010-photoshop-uxp-migration/TODO.md.
02_photoshop_setup/uxp_export/

# Step 03: SPEC 011 parity sandbox. Genuinely regenerable from the
# tagged manifest in step 02 via the Proscenio Blender importer - no
# hand-authoring sits on top, so the .blend is disposable.
#
# `doll_rigged.blend` (the rigging target) is NOT listed here: the
# armature + weight paint + actions are hand-authored work that
# cannot be regenerated by any script, so the .blend gets tracked.
# The autosave still slips through.
03_blender_setup/doll_ps_tagged.blend
03_blender_setup/doll_ps_tagged.blend1
03_blender_setup/doll_rigged.blend1
